[panting]

13
00:02:33.987 --> 00:02:35.155  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, hi there.

14
00:02:35.321 --> 00:02:37.574  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Any souvenirs to take home?

15
00:02:37.657 --> 00:02:38.658  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nope.

16
00:02:38.825 --> 00:02:40.743  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I could tell he knew something,

17
00:02:40.827 --> 00:02:42.996  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but it looks like they have
an unspoken agreement

18
00:02:43.079 --> 00:02:45.582  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to keep quiet about all of this.

19
00:02:45.665 --> 00:02:46.958  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[G.B.] Sounds rather dicey.

20
00:02:47.041 --> 00:02:48.334  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And on top of that,

21
00:02:48.418 --> 00:02:50.587  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the Guardians seem to have
sniffed us out, too.

22
00:02:50.670 --> 00:02:51.963  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They what?

23
00:02:52.130 --> 00:02:55.341  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You don't think your contact
sold you out, did he?

24
00:02:55.425 --> 00:02:58.011  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Hey, don't go around
smearing his good name.

25
00:02:58.094 --> 00:03:01.389  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We Brits take our friendships
very seriously, you know.

26
00:03:01.472 --> 00:03:02.724  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, in that case...

27
00:03:02.891 --> 00:03:04.517  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There must be someone out there

28
00:03:04.601 --> 00:03:06.227  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
who's somehow
managing to keep us

29
00:03:06.311 --> 00:03:08.229  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
under tight surveillance,
wouldn't you say?

30
00:03:08.313 --> 00:03:09.230  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[clanking]
-[gasps]

31
00:03:09.397 --> 00:03:11.149  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There they are now!

32
00:03:16.446 --> 00:03:17.488  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm.

33
00:03:19.949 --> 00:03:21.242  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Joe gasps]

34
00:03:25.204 --> 00:03:27.457  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What just happened?

35
00:03:28.917 --> 00:03:30.126  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Françoise]
Joe...

36
00:03:37.467 --> 00:03:39.469  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Françoise...

37
00:03:39.552 --> 00:03:42.889  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
what in the world
is happening to me?

38
00:03:42.972 --> 00:03:45.016  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's all right, really.

39
00:03:45.099 --> 00:03:47.143  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You realize it, too, don't you?

40
00:03:49.437 --> 00:03:51.147  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

41
00:03:56.653 --> 00:03:57.820  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Blood?

42
00:03:59.656 --> 00:04:02.033  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't you see? It's a miracle.

43
00:04:02.116 --> 00:04:04.327  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We're back to being
ordinary humans.

44
00:04:04.410 --> 00:04:06.246  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, that can't be.

45
00:04:06.329 --> 00:04:08.790  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You found what you were seeking.

46
00:04:08.957 --> 00:04:13.253  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The answer you've been looking
for is right there before you.

47
00:04:14.921 --> 00:04:18.049  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's right. Joe, think about it.

48
00:04:18.132 --> 00:04:20.802  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This is what we've
been wishing for all this time.

49
00:04:20.885 --> 00:04:23.304  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Now we can live our lives
without going into battle.

50
00:04:23.471 --> 00:04:26.849  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, but, Françoise, I...

51
00:04:28.893 --> 00:04:31.562  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Rajiv]
No need to doubt yourself.

52
00:04:31.646 --> 00:04:36.317  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You can simply accept yourself
as you are right now.

53
00:04:36.484 --> 00:04:39.779  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Joe, I feel so happy.

54
00:04:46.995 --> 00:04:48.830  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Igarashi] <i>Report your status</i>.

55
00:04:48.997 --> 00:04:51.708  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We've spotted a moving object,
and we're giving chase,

56
00:04:51.791 --> 00:04:54.210  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but we're still
not able to identify it.

57
00:04:54.377 --> 00:04:55.461  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So I see.

58
00:04:55.628 --> 00:04:58.589  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's likely 008.

59
00:04:58.673 --> 00:05:00.216  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Stand by with the depth charges!

60
00:05:00.383 --> 00:05:01.592  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Roger that.

61
00:05:05.972 --> 00:05:07.265  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Whoa.

62
00:05:11.477 --> 00:05:13.438  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Guardian]
<i>It's a counterattack!</i>

63
00:05:14.605 --> 00:05:15.815  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's no mistake.

64
00:05:15.982 --> 00:05:19.235  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I want him captured</i>
<i>immediately!</i>

65
00:05:19.319 --> 00:05:20.445  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Guardians] Roger that!

66
00:05:24.157 --> 00:05:27.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Sorry, guys. Looks like
my cover's been blown.

67
00:05:27.327 --> 00:05:29.871  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So he was just a decoy.

68
00:05:30.038 --> 00:05:31.581  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If that's the case...

69
00:05:31.748 --> 00:05:35.084  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Take the search back</i>
<i>to where you first spotted 008.</i>

70
00:05:35.168 --> 00:05:37.045  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>That's where you'll find them!</i>

71
00:05:44.385 --> 00:05:47.221  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Igarashi] <i>Catalina,</i>
<i>how's it looking on your end</i>?

72
00:05:47.305 --> 00:05:50.391  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We think we've pinpointed
009's location.

73
00:05:50.558 --> 00:05:52.769  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>We should arrive there soon.</i>

74
00:05:52.852 --> 00:05:55.354  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've got a fair number
of questions for them.

75
00:05:55.521 --> 00:05:59.025  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>If at all possible, I want you</i>
<i>to bring them back alive.</i>

76
00:05:59.108 --> 00:06:00.193  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, sir.

77
00:06:08.701 --> 00:06:10.495  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[fire crackling]

78
00:06:11.746 --> 00:06:13.539  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Does it still hurt?

79
00:06:13.623 --> 00:06:14.624  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A little.

80
00:06:14.791 --> 00:06:17.293  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I never thought to see the day

81
00:06:17.376 --> 00:06:19.087  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I would treat
your wounds like this.

82
00:06:21.255 --> 00:06:23.758  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Rajiv]
What are you so concerned about?

83
00:06:25.134 --> 00:06:28.054  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If we lose our powers
as cyborgs, what then?

84
00:06:28.137 --> 00:06:30.765  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What are we supposed
to do with our lives?

85
00:06:30.848 --> 00:06:31.849  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Françoise]
Listen.

86
00:06:31.933 --> 00:06:35.269  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You searched for a way to live
without having to fight,

87
00:06:35.353 --> 00:06:37.063  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and you have arrived
at the answer,

88
00:06:37.146 --> 00:06:38.356  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
it seems, have you not?

89
00:06:38.523 --> 00:06:40.608  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is the answer?

90
00:06:40.691 --> 00:06:42.860  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're telling me
that being a human again

91
00:06:42.944 --> 00:06:44.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
is what I really wanted?

92
00:06:44.487 --> 00:06:48.449  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You've laid down your arms
in this restoration.

93
00:06:48.533 --> 00:06:49.826  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If one bears arms,

94
00:06:49.909 --> 00:06:52.662  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
it's human nature
to want to use them.

95
00:06:52.745 --> 00:06:56.833  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Isn't that precisely why you've
been suffering all this time?

96
00:06:56.999 --> 00:06:59.001  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The only way to avoid violence

97
00:06:59.085 --> 00:07:02.296  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
is to turn my back
on my cyborg body.

98
00:07:02.380 --> 00:07:05.842  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Joe, please,
let's accept them, these bodies.

99
00:07:06.008 --> 00:07:08.761  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It is a human's
inalienable right

100
00:07:08.845 --> 00:07:11.514  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
not to bear arms
or harm another,

101
00:07:11.597 --> 00:07:14.851  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and you should just follow
your heart in these matters.

102
00:07:15.017 --> 00:07:17.103  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's right. Listen, Joe.

103
00:07:17.270 --> 00:07:19.522  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I feel so certain.

104
00:07:19.605 --> 00:07:21.774  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Being like this
will make us so much happier.

105
00:07:21.941 --> 00:07:23.901  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

106
00:07:25.153 --> 00:07:26.988  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, you could be right.

107
00:07:28.364 --> 00:07:30.992  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Jet] <i>Hey, Joe, do you copy</i>?

108
00:07:31.075 --> 00:07:32.577  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Françoise, respond!</i>

109
00:07:32.743 --> 00:07:35.496  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey, can you hear me?!

110
00:07:35.580 --> 00:07:37.331  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Something's not right here.

111
00:07:37.498 --> 00:07:39.208  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What is it?

112
00:07:39.292 --> 00:07:41.586  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Jet] Joe and the others
aren't responding.

113
00:07:41.669 --> 00:07:42.670  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're not?

114
00:07:42.753 --> 00:07:44.464  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It can't be the Blessed,
can it?

115
00:07:44.547 --> 00:07:45.548  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[explosions]
-[both gasp]

116
00:07:46.883 --> 00:07:48.259  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Dr. Gilmore]
<i>Depth charges!</i>

117
00:07:50.261 --> 00:07:53.222  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Igarashi] <i>We're only trying</i>
<i>to smoke them out of hiding</i>.

118
00:07:53.431 --> 00:07:55.016  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They'll have
to surface eventually.

119
00:07:55.099 --> 00:07:56.225  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't stop 'til then.

120
00:08:03.816 --> 00:08:05.359  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Take Ivan!
-Right!

121
00:08:05.526 --> 00:08:07.487  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thanks to what 008 did,

122
00:08:07.570 --> 00:08:10.823  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
they couldn't have gotten
a read on our exact location.

123
00:08:10.907 --> 00:08:12.825  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're dropping them at random,

124
00:08:12.909 --> 00:08:14.827  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
just waiting us out
'til we give up.

125
00:08:14.911 --> 00:08:17.538  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Let's see which one of us
can wait longer.

126
00:08:17.622 --> 00:08:19.248  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Heinrich] <i>002, what's wrong</i>?

127
00:08:19.415 --> 00:08:21.542  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps] Heinrich?

128
00:08:21.626 --> 00:08:22.835  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You know how it is.

129
00:08:22.919 --> 00:08:24.378  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Under attack
by the Guardians. You?

130
00:08:24.545 --> 00:08:27.882  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The bastards were lying in wait
for us over here, too.

131
00:08:28.049 --> 00:08:29.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you serious?

132
00:08:29.884 --> 00:08:31.969  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Joe and the others
are in trouble.

133
00:08:32.053 --> 00:08:33.804  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Geronimo]
<i>All right. What's going on?</i>

134
00:08:33.888 --> 00:08:34.889  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[both gasp]

135
00:08:35.056 --> 00:08:36.766  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Jet] <i>Geronimo</i>,

136
00:08:36.849 --> 00:08:39.477  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>those stinkin' Guardians</i>
<i>have launched an attack on us.</i>

137
00:08:39.560 --> 00:08:42.104  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Careful. They're probably</i>
<i>headed your way, too.</i>

138
00:08:42.188 --> 00:08:44.649  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I'm not getting any response</i>
<i>from Joe or Françoise.</i>

139
00:08:44.732 --> 00:08:46.651  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>You gotta get out of there</i>
<i>right now.</i>

140
00:08:48.861 --> 00:08:49.862  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

141
00:08:52.031 --> 00:08:53.407  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Geronimo?

142
00:08:53.574 --> 00:08:56.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uh, why aren't you responding

143
00:08:56.244 --> 00:08:58.412  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to Jet's
brainwave communications?

144
00:08:58.496 --> 00:08:59.830  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Eh?
-Huh?

145
00:08:59.914 --> 00:09:00.957  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We never heard them.

146
00:09:01.040 --> 00:09:02.041  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What?

147
00:09:02.208 --> 00:09:04.418  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Our powers,

148
00:09:04.502 --> 00:09:06.045  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
somehow they've gone away.

149
00:09:06.921 --> 00:09:08.047  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Eh?

150
00:09:08.214 --> 00:09:11.259  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We can't fight anymore,
not as we are now.

151
00:09:11.342 --> 00:09:15.763  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Geronimo, we now realize if we
were to lay down our arms now,

152
00:09:15.846 --> 00:09:17.557  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
then we wouldn't
have to fight anymore.

153
00:09:17.723 --> 00:09:19.350  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Eh? [grunts]

154
00:09:21.561 --> 00:09:24.355  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You monster,
what did you do to them?

155
00:09:24.522 --> 00:09:25.356  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, don't!

156
00:09:25.523 --> 00:09:27.191  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Out of my way.

157
00:09:29.902 --> 00:09:32.363  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Eh? Joe.

158
00:09:35.157 --> 00:09:37.285  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Joe, are you all right?

159
00:09:37.368 --> 00:09:39.912  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps] Geronimo...

160
00:09:39.996 --> 00:09:41.205  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
that hurt me.

161
00:09:41.372 --> 00:09:42.832  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

162
00:09:42.999 --> 00:09:44.917  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's strange.

163
00:09:45.001 --> 00:09:47.878  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'd forgotten
what pain like this felt like.

164
00:09:55.553 --> 00:09:57.722  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Squad, prepare for descent.

165
00:09:57.805 --> 00:09:59.390  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Commence operation!

166
00:09:59.473 --> 00:10:01.142  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
As soon as you find the cyborgs,

167
00:10:01.309 --> 00:10:03.019  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
you have the green light
to terminate.

168
00:10:03.102 --> 00:10:04.103  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Guardians] Roger that!

169
00:10:04.270 --> 00:10:09.108  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Geronimo]
Joe, Françoise, open your eyes!

170
00:10:09.275 --> 00:10:11.068  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You can rest assured.

171
00:10:11.152 --> 00:10:12.695  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're in transition.

172
00:10:12.778 --> 00:10:14.614  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They'll soon
complete their choice.

173
00:10:15.531 --> 00:10:18.451  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Should they live on
as human beings now

174
00:10:18.534 --> 00:10:21.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
or continue their
existence as cyborgs?

175
00:10:25.041 --> 00:10:27.376  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's no need
to make that choice.

176
00:10:27.543 --> 00:10:31.255  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh? And what
do you mean by that?

177
00:10:31.422 --> 00:10:32.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Great Spirit,

178
00:10:32.923 --> 00:10:35.968  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He was the one who gave us
these physical bodies.

179
00:10:36.052 --> 00:10:38.387  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Understand?
They weren't ours to begin with.

180
00:10:38.554 --> 00:10:41.641  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Are you saying
even a modified body

181
00:10:41.724 --> 00:10:43.184  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
will never lose sight

182
00:10:43.267 --> 00:10:45.978  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
of its true will and purpose
in this world?

183
00:10:50.149 --> 00:10:52.985  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We are just like
the ship of Theseus.

184
00:10:53.069 --> 00:10:55.696  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
However our bodies
might be refashioned,

185
00:10:55.780 --> 00:10:58.324  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
so long as we
hold on to our souls,

186
00:10:58.407 --> 00:11:01.452  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
we will remain who we are,
no matter what occurs.

187
00:11:05.539 --> 00:11:07.458  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gunfire]

188
00:11:13.047 --> 00:11:14.256  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're here.

189
00:11:15.341 --> 00:11:16.384  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

190
00:11:26.769 --> 00:11:27.812  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunts]

191
00:11:45.287 --> 00:11:47.039  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[suit whirs]

192
00:11:48.791 --> 00:11:50.376  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've got the advantage,

193
00:11:50.459 --> 00:11:53.254  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
way more experience
in underwater combat.

194
00:12:00.636 --> 00:12:01.846  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[inhales]

195
00:12:03.472 --> 00:12:04.557  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

196
00:12:04.640 --> 00:12:06.934  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So they did spot us after all.

197
00:12:08.018 --> 00:12:09.937  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No choice.
I have to shoot it down.

198
00:12:11.480 --> 00:12:12.857  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gurgles]

199
00:12:15.151 --> 00:12:16.485  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I let my guard down.

200
00:12:16.652 --> 00:12:19.196  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
008, come in. What's going on?

201
00:12:19.280 --> 00:12:20.364  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Sorry, you guys.</i>

202
00:12:20.448 --> 00:12:21.907  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I was totally</i>
<i>taken by surprise.</i>

203
00:12:21.991 --> 00:12:22.992  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[groans]

204
00:12:23.159 --> 00:12:25.494  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now what are we gonna do?

205
00:12:25.661 --> 00:12:28.122  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'll go talk to them,
cut a deal.

206
00:12:28.205 --> 00:12:29.331  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What?!

207
00:12:29.415 --> 00:12:31.542  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've noticed
that whenever you go out,

208
00:12:31.625 --> 00:12:34.211  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
it never really ends
with just a talk, you know?

209
00:12:34.295 --> 00:12:36.088  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, whatever.
That's up to them!

210
00:12:57.359 --> 00:12:58.986  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

211
00:13:23.469 --> 00:13:25.012  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're under arrest

212
00:13:25.095 --> 00:13:28.307  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
for violating the International
Terrorism Prevention Act.

213
00:13:28.390 --> 00:13:30.809  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I want you all
to surrender at once.

214
00:13:30.976 --> 00:13:32.228  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Heh.

215
00:13:32.311 --> 00:13:35.397  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Unfortunately, the others
are out right now.

216
00:13:35.481 --> 00:13:37.316  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm holding down the fort
by myself.

217
00:13:37.483 --> 00:13:42.821  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
001, 006, I know the Doctor
and Lucy are both in there.

218
00:13:42.988 --> 00:13:46.033  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So you see right through me,
is that it?

219
00:13:46.116 --> 00:13:47.826  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
As a matter of fact,
you're right.

220
00:13:47.910 --> 00:13:49.828  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Now stop resisting,
and do as I say!

221
00:13:49.995 --> 00:13:51.580  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Gotta give you props

222
00:13:51.664 --> 00:13:54.333  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
for having more
than one brain cell, my friend,

223
00:13:54.500 --> 00:13:57.586  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but you still
don't get it, do you?

224
00:13:57.670 --> 00:13:59.088  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't get what?

225
00:13:59.255 --> 00:14:02.049  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're wasting your time
on this path, you know.

226
00:14:02.132 --> 00:14:05.010  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Open your eyes, and see
who your true enemy is!

227
00:14:06.262 --> 00:14:07.972  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I bet that struck a chord.

228
00:14:08.055 --> 00:14:09.056  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Am I right?

229
00:14:09.139 --> 00:14:11.100  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

230
00:14:11.183 --> 00:14:12.893  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Seems maybe
I should at least listen

231
00:14:12.977 --> 00:14:15.396  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to what you people
have to say about all this.

232
00:14:15.479 --> 00:14:17.898  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Except not out here.
At headquarters!

233
00:14:18.065 --> 00:14:20.484  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If you think I'm gonna
let you haul me off

234
00:14:20.568 --> 00:14:22.278  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to a place like that,
you're crazy.

235
00:14:22.361 --> 00:14:24.822  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Enough of this. Take them in!

236
00:14:26.031 --> 00:14:27.032  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[groans]

237
00:14:46.886 --> 00:14:50.222  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

238
00:14:50.389 --> 00:14:51.974  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What are
the Guardians doing here?

239
00:14:52.057 --> 00:14:54.184  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Do you think they've
come to arrest us?

240
00:14:54.351 --> 00:14:58.147  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No. What I believe they intend
is to kill us where we stand.

241
00:15:03.903 --> 00:15:05.112  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[both gasp]

242
00:15:05.195 --> 00:15:06.196  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Joe] Geronimo!

243
00:15:07.197 --> 00:15:08.198  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you...

244
00:15:09.366 --> 00:15:11.368  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunts]

245
00:15:11.452 --> 00:15:15.205  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Listen.
You're a warrior of justice.

246
00:15:16.373 --> 00:15:18.834  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I believe in you, Joe.

247
00:15:22.087 --> 00:15:24.673  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[yells]

248
00:15:40.898 --> 00:15:44.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[yells]

249
00:15:47.404 --> 00:15:49.031  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
With our bodies weak as this,

250
00:15:49.114 --> 00:15:52.076  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
it would just take one bullet,
and we'd be no more.

251
00:15:52.159 --> 00:15:54.203  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Rajiv] So you are going?

252
00:16:02.920 --> 00:16:04.088  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have to.

253
00:16:05.422 --> 00:16:07.508  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I can't leave my friend to die.

254
00:16:07.591 --> 00:16:08.842  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No! Don't do it!

255
00:16:09.009 --> 00:16:11.011  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do you want to help your friend?

256
00:16:11.095 --> 00:16:12.304  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Is that your answer then?

257
00:16:14.098 --> 00:16:15.140  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Wait!

258
00:16:16.350 --> 00:16:17.977  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

259
00:16:20.437 --> 00:16:22.773  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunts]

260
00:16:22.856 --> 00:16:24.942  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Geronimo! I'll fight with you!

261
00:16:25.109 --> 00:16:26.485  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Joe!

262
00:16:46.171 --> 00:16:48.507  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Françoise! Get out of there!

263
00:17:08.110 --> 00:17:09.987  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Damn it. Let me go!

264
00:17:10.070 --> 00:17:11.405  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[groans]

265
00:17:11.488 --> 00:17:14.783  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This game ends now, 002.

266
00:17:16.285 --> 00:17:17.286  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Eh?

267
00:17:24.501 --> 00:17:27.004  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[yells]

268
00:17:34.219 --> 00:17:36.263  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Accelerator!

269
00:17:46.732 --> 00:17:48.108  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why?

270
00:17:53.113 --> 00:17:55.574  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Is this really
the future I wanted?

271
00:17:55.741 --> 00:17:58.035  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Is this my answer?

272
00:18:06.502 --> 00:18:09.546  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Joe] It can't be.
This can't be it!

273
00:18:09.630 --> 00:18:12.925  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
All I wanted was to save
everyone from having to fight!

274
00:18:14.718 --> 00:18:17.346  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Françoise!

275
00:18:17.429 --> 00:18:19.348  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[crackling]

276
00:18:30.901 --> 00:18:33.362  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[hum]

277
00:18:59.179 --> 00:19:00.764  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Joe] What is this?

278
00:19:06.145 --> 00:19:08.772  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps] What was that?

279
00:19:14.486 --> 00:19:16.697  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Joe, thank you.

280
00:19:17.781 --> 00:19:19.616  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
At that moment,

281
00:19:19.700 --> 00:19:22.619  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
for the first time,
I wanted my Accelerator.

282
00:19:23.579 --> 00:19:25.330  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Françoise] And is that...

283
00:19:25.414 --> 00:19:27.291  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
the answer you were looking for?

284
00:19:27.374 --> 00:19:28.375  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Joe] Yes.

285
00:19:29.585 --> 00:19:31.003  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So that's it then.

286
00:19:31.086 --> 00:19:32.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Staying in the fight
is our destiny.

287
00:19:35.257 --> 00:19:37.176  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I think it just might be.

288
00:19:44.808 --> 00:19:46.101  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[yells]

289
00:19:56.069 --> 00:19:58.697  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Looks like somebody's
back in action, aren't they?

290
00:19:58.780 --> 00:20:00.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah.

291
00:20:00.324 --> 00:20:02.201  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I didn't mean to make you worry.

292
00:20:02.284 --> 00:20:03.952  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm sorry.

293
00:20:04.036 --> 00:20:06.997  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Rajiv] Have you found
your true answer, then?

294
00:20:08.165 --> 00:20:10.584  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you truly certain?

295
00:20:12.002 --> 00:20:13.921  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You might modify our bodies,

296
00:20:14.004 --> 00:20:17.216  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but nothing in this world
can change our souls.

297
00:20:18.634 --> 00:20:20.886  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If I'm going to save
all those I can,

298
00:20:21.053 --> 00:20:23.931  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
then both this body
and this power...

299
00:20:25.140 --> 00:20:27.351  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
are an important part of me.

300
00:20:29.645 --> 00:20:31.188  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So be it, then.

301
00:20:31.271 --> 00:20:33.148  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Looks like we won't avoid war.

302
00:20:35.317 --> 00:20:37.069  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sir, I...

303
00:20:37.236 --> 00:20:41.281  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Be true. Follow your heart, 009.

304
00:20:41.448 --> 00:20:42.407  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Huh?

305
00:20:42.491 --> 00:20:43.450  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Geronimo] Oh?

306
00:20:49.831 --> 00:20:51.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So his power must be...

307
00:20:51.416 --> 00:20:55.045  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
To shine a light
on the doubts in one's heart

308
00:20:55.128 --> 00:20:58.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and, through mere illusions,
to lead one to one's choice.

309
00:20:59.007 --> 00:21:02.594  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So even the pain I felt,
that was an illusion.

310
00:21:02.678 --> 00:21:04.638  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And if so...

311
00:21:07.849 --> 00:21:08.850  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

312
00:21:18.068 --> 00:21:21.238  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
009, his power
can't be explained

313
00:21:21.321 --> 00:21:23.824  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
simply because he's equipped
with an Accelerator.

314
00:21:29.997 --> 00:21:30.998  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunts]

315
00:21:34.543 --> 00:21:36.962  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jet. Chang Changku.

316
00:21:37.045 --> 00:21:38.714  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sorry about all of this.

317
00:21:38.797 --> 00:21:40.882  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jet's a pretty lousy negotiator.

318
00:21:41.049 --> 00:21:43.218  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, pardon me
for actually trying something.

319
00:21:43.302 --> 00:21:44.386  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[groans]

320
00:21:44.553 --> 00:21:46.346  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Take them away!

321
00:21:47.431 --> 00:21:48.932  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[whirring]

322
00:21:55.814 --> 00:21:56.982  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[both gasp]

323
00:21:57.065 --> 00:21:58.066  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[yells]

324
00:21:58.150 --> 00:21:59.151  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[rifle fires]

325
00:21:59.318 --> 00:22:01.611  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Hey! What the hell
are you doing?!

326
00:22:02.738 --> 00:22:03.947  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Lucy yells]

327
00:22:08.160 --> 00:22:09.786  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's going on here?

328
00:22:09.870 --> 00:22:10.996  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Blessed?

329
00:22:11.163 --> 00:22:12.205  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The what?

330
00:22:20.172 --> 00:22:21.381  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Get me out of these.

331
00:22:21.465 --> 00:22:22.382  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll get him!

332
00:22:23.633 --> 00:22:24.676  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Jet] <i>Joe</i>!

333
00:22:24.760 --> 00:22:26.053  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's the matter, Jet?

334
00:22:26.136 --> 00:22:27.679  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Joe, they took Ivan!</i>

335
00:22:27.763 --> 00:22:28.764  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Geronimo] What?!

336
00:22:28.847 --> 00:22:29.848  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you sure?

337
00:22:29.931 --> 00:22:31.850  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Joe, why don't you go on ahead?

338
00:22:31.933 --> 00:22:33.185  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hurry back to the Dolphin.

339
00:22:33.351 --> 00:22:34.561  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, yeah.

340
00:22:35.645 --> 00:22:36.855  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Accelerator!

341
00:22:44.446 --> 00:22:46.281  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No doubts anymore.

342
00:22:46.448 --> 00:22:48.950  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Joe] <i>You guys, wait for me</i>.

343
00:22:54.956 --> 00:22:56.958  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[ballad playing]

344
00:23:04.883 --> 00:23:06.885  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[singing in Japanese]

